      ('The Meme',
        'The Meme is a bright nightmare or a dark daydream dragged out of the far corners of the culture,
        a joke that goes bump in the night. The Meme is the unspeakable spoken as cliché,
        the stereotype raised to the status of art. The meme is all thats wrong with that thing you love,
        and everything thats good about that thing you hate. The Meme like fiction, is the little lie
        that sometimes tells a larger truth. The Meme can question Authority or speak on Authoritys behalf.
        The Meme is clever but cruel: its all fun and games until its your face on 4chan.',
